<item>
 <title>2.7 Starting Work</title>
 <link>https://www.middlebury.edu/old-about/old-handbook/handbook_archive/handbook-2017-2018/ug-college-policies/employee/employment/starting_work/node/583559</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;When employees first report to work, their supervisors will show them the workplace, explain the responsibilities and procedures of the position, and answer any questions they might have.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additionally, new employees will receive information from their supervisors about paychecks, College IDs, College policies regarding overtime, CTO, sick leave reserve, attendance, performance evaluations, and wage reviews; keeping records current; automobile registration and parking; arrangements for necessary keys; lunch schedules and facilities; any required training associated with the position; and campus orientation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supervisors should access the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.middlebury.edu/media/view/292393/original/hiring_supervisor_checklist.pdf&quot;&gt;Supervisor Check List&lt;/a&gt; for new employee orientation suggestions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
